  "body": "Following eth_getLogs request\r\n```\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getLogs\",\"params\":[{\"fromBlock\": \"0x1147f5b\", \"toBlock\": \"0x114872b\"}],\"id\":0}\r\n```\r\nTakes more than a minute to complete on my erigon node on the first run. Geth/Alchemy respond in under 5s\r\n\r\nIt seems that erigon has some caching happening under the hood. However, such response times on cold cache make indexing via erigon very hard. Are such long response times expected or am I doing something wrong?",
